      "date": "2026-06-06",
      "rating": 1,
      "title": "Gross, go with the chicken",
      "text": "I have had other Kevin’s meals and generally found they are not the most flavorful but I like the ingredients and that it’s a convenience item that still falls Within how I choose to eat. When I saw the reviews I ignored them because sometimes choosing health doesn’t taste as flavorful but if it is fueling your body and half decent, sometimes that’s good enough for a busy working mom…This meal on the other hand was so god awful I feel like it should never have made it past R&D testing. I would liken the texture to one big dog food clump and the steak tastes like it came from a can (not su vide). The gravy was probably the most foul gravy I’ve ever had, season less and yet also salty with a hint of funk (I’m guessing from mushroom powder?) I tried saving it by sautéing some kale and adding some other seasoning to try and revive the dish but it was just bad, texture was bad, flavor was bad and I greatly disliked eating it giving my second portion to my dogs. I will never waste my money on Kevin’s steak again- for those who enjoy other Kevin’s dishes, just stick with the chicken meals!",
      "capture": "public retailer review",
