      "title": "Mars Co. bought them out and ruined a good quality meal.",
      "text": "Being a family who has celiac with lactose intolerance we have always loved Kevin's Meals. Unfortunately, over the past two years, the quality of Kevin's meals have significantly decreased. Not only are the portions smaller, the quality of meat has significantly declined all while the prices went from $7.99 to a whopping $12.99. This last meal was total junk. Meat was truly awful, chewy, stringy. Most the sauce evaporated. Just junk. Low amd behold, after some research, I found Mars Corp acquired them back in 2023. THIS EXPLAINS SOOOO MUCH. Everything that company you hes, turns to crap..and they own everything. From many, many foods and candy, to your dog's food, vet, emergency vet, vet insurance and stock in medicine. So tired of corporations like Mars ruining a good thing.",
